      "type": "answer",
      "text": "To launch these Frappe UI components, you'll need to:\n\n## 📋 **Prerequisites**\n\n1. **Frappe Development Environment** - Frappe framework installed locally or in cloud\n2. **Frappe App Setup** - Create a new app or integrate into existing app\n3. **Component Registration** - Register components in Frappe's UI components registry\n\n## 🚀 **Launch Steps**\n\n### 1. **Frappe App Structure**\n```bash\nyour-app/\n├── src/\n│   ├── fg_companion/\n│   │   ├── FGCompanionStore.ts\n│   │   ├── FGCompanionStoreTest.vue\n│   │   └── README.md\n│   └── frappe_ui_components.js  # Import and register components\n```\n\n### 2. **Register Components in Frappe**\nCreate `frappe_ui_components.js` to register your Frappe UI components:\n```javascript\nimport { FGCompanionStore, FGCompanionStoreTest } from './fg_companion/';\n\n// Register components with Frappe UI\nfrappe.ui.components.register({\n  FGCompanionStore,\n  FGCompanionStoreTest\n});\n```\n\n### 3. **Integrate with Frappe Backend**\nYou'll need Frappe API endpoints for:\n- `fg_companion.api.get_events`\n- `raven_channel.get_all_channels`  \n- `lms.utils.get_courses`\n- `raven_channel.create_direct_message_channel`\n\n### 4. **Use in Frappe Pages**\n```vue\n<!-- In any Frappe Desk page -->\n<FrappeButton \n  data-slot=\"trigger\"\n  data-variant=\"solid\"\n  @click=\"loadEvents\"\n>\n  Load Events\n</FrappeButton>\n\n<!-- Include your component -->\n<FGCompanionStoreTest />\n```\n\n## 🌐 **Frappe Development Server**\n\nTo run Frappe development environment:\n```bash\n# If you have Frappe Bench setup\ncd ~/frappe-bench\nbench start\n\n# Or install Frappe locally\npip install frappe\nfrappe --version\n```\n\n## 📝 **Next Steps**\n\n1. **Set up Frappe development environment**\n2. **Create a Frappe app** or integrate into existing one\n3. **Register the components** with Frappe UI\n4. **Create backend API endpoints** for the store operations\n5. **Add the component** to a Frappe Desk page or report\n\n## 🔧 **Troubleshooting**\n\n**Common issues:**\n- Component not rendering → Check Frappe UI installation\n- API calls failing → Verify backend endpoints exist\n- Event handling not working → Check Frappe event system integration\n\nThe components are Frappe UI compliant and ready for integration once you have the Frappe environment set up. Would you like help with any specific part of this setup process?",
