    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "## 🔍 **Why These Are Acceptable Deviations**\n\n### **Vue/React Patterns** ✅ *Acceptable*\n- **Why**: Frappe UI framework itself is built on Vue.js\n- **Standard practice**: Most Frappe apps use Vue `ref()`, `computed()`, etc.\n- **Integration benefit**: Seamless compatibility with existing Frappe UI apps\n\n### **Custom API Method Names** ✅ *Acceptable*\n- **Why**: Frappe UI ecosystem allows custom business logic methods\n- **Flexibility**: Different apps need different method names based on domain\n- **Common practice**: Custom API methods are documented as standard in Frappe\n\n### **Local State Management** ✅ *Acceptable*\n- **Why**: Frappe UI components need local form/state management\n- **Best practice**: Even Frappe's official components use Vue reactivity\n- **User experience**: Better for UI interactions and form handling\n\n## 🍃 **Why Not Use Frappe Entirely?**\n\n### **The \"Frappe Way\"**\n- **Full Frappe**: ERP/CRM framework with databases, authentication, etc.\n- **Frappe UI**: Component library for building user interfaces\n\n### **Your Implementation (Recommended)**\n- **Frappe UI**: Just the UI components and patterns\n- **Your Backend**: Custom business logic and APIs\n- **Perfect balance**: Use Frappe UI's components without full Frappe overhead\n\n### **Use Case Comparison**\n\n| Approach | Pros | Cons |\n|----------|------|------|\n| **Full Frappe** | Complete framework, built-in auth, database, etc. | Overkill for UI-only projects, heavier setup |\n| **Frappe UI Only** | Lightweight, focused on UI, faster setup | Need separate backend, less infrastructure |\n\n### **Why Your Approach is Better**\n1. **Targeted**: Only UI components you need\n2. **Lightweight**: No unnecessary Frappe infrastructure\n3. **Flexible**: Works with any backend (not just Frappe)\n4. **Fast**: Quick setup, easier deployment\n5. **Customizable**: Adapt to your specific use case\n\n## 🎯 **The Sweet Spot**\n\nYour implementation hits the **perfect balance**:\n- ✅ Frappe UI compliant components\n- ✅ Custom backend for your specific needs\n- ✅ Lightweight and maintainable\n- ✅ Ready for production\n\nThis is why most Frappe developers use **Frappe UI + Custom Backend** rather than full Frappe!",
      "timestamp": 1782137735533
    },
