      "type": "answer",
      "text": "## 🔍 **Environment Check Results**\n\nI found an important clarification - **we're not in WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux)**. You're in a **Windows PowerShell environment**.\n\n## 📋 **Current Status**\n\n**Frappe is now installed** in your Windows Python environment, but:\n\n### ❌ **Not Recommended Setup**\n```python\n# Frappe version: 0.0.1 (very old!)\n# Installed via: pip install frappe\n```\n\n**Frappe warns:** `\"frappe package is installed from PyPI, which isn't supported\"`\n\n## 🚀 **Correct Frappe Installation Methods**\n\n### **For WSL/Linux (Recommended)**\n```bash\n# Using Frappe Bench\ncurl -fsSL https://deb.bintray.com/frappe/bench | sh\nbench init my-bench\ncd my-bench\nbench setup\nbench new-site site.local\n\n# Using Docker (easier)\ndocker run -ti --rm frappe/frappe-bench\n```\n\n### **In Your Current Windows PowerShell**\n```bash\n# Install Frappe Bench (better than pip)\npip install frappe-bench\nbench init my-bench\n```\n\n## 🌐 **WSL-Specific Steps for Your Use Case**\n\n### **1. If You're in WSL (Linux Subsystem)**\n```bash\n# Navigate to your fg_companion app directory\ncd /path/to/your-app\n\n# Install Frappe via proper channel\ncurl -fsSL https://deb.bintray.com/frappe/bench | sh\nbench init my-bench\ncd my-bench\n\n# Install your fg_companion app\nbench get-app fg_companion https://github.com/andiekobbie/my-bench\n\n# Set up the site\nbench new-site site.local\nbench --site site.local install-app fg_companion\n```\n\n### **2. In Windows PowerShell (Current Environment)**\n```bash\n# Install Frappe Bench\npip install frappe-bench\n\n# Create a new bench\nbench init my-bench\n\n# Navigate to bench\ncd my-bench\n\n# Install your app from current directory\nbench get-app .  # or use path to your repo\n```\n\n## 📝 **Your Next Steps**\n\n### **To Launch with Frappe:**\n\n1. **If you have WSL (recommended):**\n   - Install Frappe via `curl -fsSL https://deb.bintray.com/frappe/bench | sh`\n   - Set up Frappe Bench with your `fg_companion` app\n\n2. **If you're in Windows PowerShell:**\n   - Install `frappe-bench` via pip\n   - Create a Frappe Bench environment\n\n### **Alternative - Local Testing**\nFor now, you can test your Frappe UI components locally by:\n- Keeping them in your current directory\n- Creating simple HTML/JS wrappers for testing\n- Using your backend APIs directly\n\n## 🔄 **Recommended Path**\n\nSince your Frappe UI components are designed to work with **any backend**, you could:\n1. **Short-term**: Test them with mock APIs locally\n2. **Long-term**: Set up Frappe Bench in WSL for proper Frappe integration\n\nThe components are Frappe UI compliant and ready once you have a proper Frappe environment! 🚀",
      "timestamp": 1782137813303
    },
