      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is asking about Frappe in WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux) environment. From my investigation, I'm actually in a Windows PowerShell environment, not WSL. \n\nLet me explain the situation:\n1. I'm in Windows PowerShell on a Windows system\n2. The user is asking about WSL (which is a Linux environment on Windows)\n3. I just installed Frappe via pip in this Windows Python environment\n4. But this isn't actually WSL - it's Windows PowerShell\n\nI should explain this and tell them that what they need is actually to set up a proper Frappe environment, either in WSL or using Frappe Bench.\n\nThe key points:\n- I'm in Windows PowerShell, not WSL\n- Frappe installed via pip is not the recommended way to use Frappe\n- Frappe is typically installed using Frappe Bench or Docker\n- For production use, they should use Frappe Bench or Frappe Docker\n\nLet me provide this explanation clearly.",
