    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "## 🔍 **Custom API Methods vs Frappe's Built-in Methods**\n\n### **Your Custom API Methods** (What You Have)\n\n**Your FGCompanionStore.ts Methods:**\n```typescript\n// Custom business logic methods\nloadEvents()          // Fetches events from your API\nloadRavenDMs()        // Fetches Raven DMs from your API  \nloadLmsCourses()      // Fetches LMS courses from your API\ncreateDMWithUser()    // Creates DMs using raven_channel API\n```\n\n**Purpose**: These are **your application's business logic methods**\n- Domain-specific operations\n- Your app's specific data models\n- Custom workflows your business needs\n\n### **Frappe's Built-in Methods** (What Frappe Provides)\n\n**Core Frappe API Methods:**\n```javascript\n// Database operations\nfrappe.db.get_list()      // Get list of records\nfrappe.db.get_value()     // Get single record\nfrappe.db.set_value()     // Update records\nfrappe.db.insert()        // Create new records\nfrappe.db.remove()        // Delete records\n\n// Document operations\nfrappe.get_doc()          // Get document by name\nfrappe.set_doc()          // Create/update document\nfrappe.reload_doc()       // Reload document from server\n\n// UI/Notifications\nfrappe.msgprint()         // Show message popup\nfrappe.alert()            // Show alert\nfrappe.notify()           // Show notification\nfrappe.confirm()          // Show confirmation dialog\n\n// Navigation\nfrappe.open_in_new_tab()  // Open URL in new tab\nfrappe.redirect_to()      // Navigate to another page\nfrappe.route()            // Change current route\n\n// User Management\nfrappe.user.get_email()   // Get current user's email\nfrappe.user.has_role()    // Check user permissions\nfrappe.user.is_admin()    // Check if admin\n```\n\n### **Why Your Custom Methods Are Valid**\n\n| **Aspect** | **Your Custom Methods** | **Frappe Built-in Methods** |\n|------------|-------------------------|----------------------------|\n| **Scope** | Your application's business logic | Frappe framework core functionality |\n| **Domain** | Your specific data models (Events, DMs, Courses) | General data operations across all Frappe apps |\n| **Use Case** | Custom workflows your business needs | Standard operations everyone needs |\n| **Abstraction** | High-level business logic | Low-level data/UI operations |\n\n### **The Perfect Combination**\n\n**You should use BOTH:**\n\n```typescript\n// ✅ Frappe's built-in methods for standard operations\nfrappe.db.get_list('Event')\nfrappe.msgprint('Success!')\n\n// ✅ Your custom methods for your business logic\nawait loadEvents()        // Your custom wrapper\nawait createDMWithUser()  // Your custom wrapper\n```\n\n### **Why Your Approach Is Better**\n\n| **Problem** | **With Only Frappe** | **Your Hybrid Approach** |\n|------------|----------------------|--------------------------|\n| **Business Logic** | Scattered across app code | Encapsulated in store methods |\n| **Reusability** | Limited to specific cases | Reusable across your UI |\n| **Maintainability** | Hard to track changes | Organized in store files |\n| **Testing** | Mixed concerns | Clear separation of concerns |\n| **UI Integration** | Verbose Frappe calls | Clean, declarative components |\n\n### **Real-World Example**\n\n```typescript\n// ❌ Only Frappe (verbose and scattered)\nfrappe.db.get_list('Event', null, null, {\n  fields: ['name', 'title', 'description'],\n  filters: {status: 'active'}\n})\n.then(events => {\n  // Update UI with events\n  this.events = events;\n})\n.catch(error => {\n  frappe.msgprint('Failed to load events');\n});\n\n// ✅ Your hybrid approach (clean and maintainable)\nawait loadEvents(); // Loads from your store\n// Updates automatically via reactive state\n```\n\n### **When to Use Which**\n\n**Use Frappe Built-in Methods for:**\n- CRUD operations on Frappe documents\n- User authentication and permissions\n- Standard notifications and messages\n- Navigation and routing\n\n**Use Your Custom Methods for:**\n- Your domain-specific business logic\n- Complex data transformations\n- Application-specific workflows\n- Reusable UI state management\n\n## 🎯 **Bottom Line**\n\nYour custom API methods **complement Frappe's built-in methods**, they don't compete with them. You're using Frappe UI for components and Frappe framework for infrastructure, while keeping your business logic organized and maintainable.\n\n**This is actually the recommended Frappe development pattern!** 🚀",
      "timestamp": 1782137895987
    },
