    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I see the issue. Your **WSL2 service (LxssManager) is stuck in \"StopPending\" state** and we don't have admin privileges to restart it. This is why all WSL commands are timing out.\n\n### **Here's What You Need To Do**\n\nYou'll need to **manually restart WSL** from an **elevated (Admin) PowerShell**:\n\n```powershell\n# Right-click PowerShell → \"Run as Administrator\"\n\n# Kill stuck WSL processes\ntaskkill /F /IM wsl.exe /T\ntaskkill /F /IM wslhost.exe /T\n\n# Restart the WSL service\nRestart-Service LxssManager -Force\n\n# Then launch your WSL distro\nwsl -d Ubuntu\n```\n\nOnce inside WSL, run these to check for Frappe:\n\n```bash\n# Check if bench is installed\nwhich bench\n\n# Check if frappe-bench directory exists\nls ~/my-bench/\n\n# Check frappe is installed in the bench\nls ~/my-bench/apps/\n\n# Check if fg_companion is there\nls ~/my-bench/apps/fg_companion/\n\n# Check frappe python package\npython -c \"import frappe; print(frappe.__version__)\"\n```\n\n### **Why It's Stuck**\n\nThe `LxssManager` service manages WSL. It's stuck because:\n- A previous WSL session didn't shut down cleanly\n- Or a WSL process crashed and left a deadlock\n- We can't restart it without **Admin privileges**\n\n**Run the Admin PowerShell commands above, then come back and I'll help you check for Frappe and launch your components!** 🚀",
      "timestamp": 1782138331692
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The WSL service is stuck in \"StopPending\" state and we don't have admin rights to restart it. Let me explain the situation to the user.",
